@NODE Introduction "Introduction"

 @{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

 Icon Master is nothing more than just another icon copier. Though there
 are many similar tools, this one has several features which make it
 different from them. These are: ability to copy, swap, remove and create
 default icons, work with old and new icons, separate places for source
 and destination icon and unlimited size of the icons.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements "Requirements"

 @{b}@{u}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

 The program requires:

 - Workbench 3.0
 - MUI 3.8
 - utilities.library 1.1 (included)
@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation "Installation"

 @{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

 To install this program just run the installation program from the
 "Install" directory.
@ENDNODE

@NODE Menus "Menus"

 @{b}@{u}Menus@{ub}@{uu}

 Program:

   - Informations...  Show informations about program
   - Hide             Hide
   - Quit             Quit

 Options:

   - Copy          Copy icons
   - Swap          Swap icons
   - Create        Create default icons
   - Remove        Remove icons

   - Old images    Perform actions on old icons
   - New images    Perform actions on new icons

   - Save options  Save options

 MUI:

   - Informations...  Show informations about MUI
   - Settings...      Edit MUI settings
@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "Usage"

 @{b}@{u}Usage@{uu}@{ub}

 To copy icon drag source icon to "Source" and destination icons
 to "Destination".

 To swap icons drag first icon to "Source" and second icon to
 "Destination".

 To remove or to create default icons just drag destination
 icons to "Destination".

 Warning: removing old icon will cause removing whole ".info"
          file.

 If the source icon has both old and new images, you may change
 currently displayed image by pressing the left mouse button on
 the "Source".

 "Req..." buttons are used to open a reqeuster.
@ENDNODE

@NODE History "History"

 @{b}@{u}History@{ub}@{uu}

 1.1:

 - icons can now be selected with requester
 - installator has been added
 - default disk icons are now correctly opened
 - window's size automatically changes when icons are too big to fit
   into it
 - documentation has been rewritten to AmigaGuide

 1.0:

 - first release
@ENDNODE

